  "body": "**Description**\r\nAfter an enforced shutdown (e.g. power outage), the following exception keeps on reoccurring:\r\n`Processing loop threw an exception. Block: 16789026 (0x12bef8...eb28c6), Exception: System.InvalidOperationException: Attempted to process a blockchain without having starting state\r\n   at Nethermind.Consensus.Processing.BlockchainProcessor.PrepareBlocksToProcess(Block suggestedBlock, ProcessingOptions options, ProcessingBranch processingBranch)\r\n   at Nethermind.Consensus.Processing.BlockchainProcessor.Process(Block suggestedBlock, ProcessingOptions options, IBlockTracer tracer)\r\n   at Nethermind.Consensus.Processing.BlockchainProcessor.RunProcessingLoop()`\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n1. Enforce shutdown of the node\r\n2. Start again\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\nException thrown during block processing.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nAny workaround? Can the issue be avoided in case of unexpected shutdown.\r\n\r\n**Logs**\r\nAttached\r\n[mainnet.logs.txt](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/10966704/mainnet.logs.txt)\r\n",
